569. Acad Med. 2005 Apr;80(4):352-5. doi: 10.1097/00001888-200504000-00009.

A course on the transition to adult care of patients with childhood-onset 
chronic illnesses.

Hagood JS(1), Lenker CV, Thrasher S.

Author information:
(1)University of Alabama School of Medicine, University of Alabama at 
Birmingham, Department of Pediatrics, AL, USA. JHagood@peds.uab.edu

Children with special health care needs born today have a 90% chance of 
surviving into adulthood, making their transition to adult systems of care an 
issue that will affect almost all physicians. However, many adult generalists 
and specialists are not familiar with the management of chronic diseases that 
begin in childhood. While the public health system has made transition to 
appropriate adult care a priority, and many specialty organizations have 
endorsed this concept, there are no published studies addressing how the concept 
